==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Roust
<hw>Roust</hw> <pr>(roust)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <def>To rouse; to
disturb; <as>as, to <ex>roust</ex> one out</as>.</def> <mark>[Prov. Eng.
& Local, U.S.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Roust</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Roust
<hw>Roust</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Cf. Icel. <ets>r⟦oum⟧st</ets> an
estuary.]</ety> <def>A strong tide or current, especially in a narrow
channel.</def> <altsp>[Written also <asp>rost</asp>, and
<asp>roost</asp>.]</altsp> <rj><au>Jamieson.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Roustabout</ent>⟦br⟧
